Source: rhtvision
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ivan Baldo <lubaldo@adinet.com.uy>
Standards-Version: 2.4.0.0

Package: rhtvision1-dev
Architecture: i386
Depends: rhtvision1, libc6-dev, libgpmg1-dev, libncurses4-dev
Provides: rhtvision-dev
Conflicts: rhtvision-dev
Description: Development files for the RHTVision library - a TUI interface.
 This is the statically linked library and header files for the development
 of applications using the RHTVision library. You need to install this package
 only if you want to develop or compile programs using the RHTVision library.

Package: rhtvision1
Architecture: i386
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: The RHTVision library - an intuitive TUI interface for console applications.
 This is the shared library for programs using the RHTVision library.
 .
 The RHTVision library gives an intuitive and user friendly TUI (Textual User
 Interface) for programs using this library and running in a console.
 .
 This library is based on the Turbo Vision library made by Borland Corporation.
 That library was released by Borland under a Public Domain license.
 RHTVision is Borland's Turbo Vision library but with enhancements, some
 changes and a GPL license.
 .
 There's a DOS version of this library as well.
 
